text: A very balanced yet tasty bowl of mee-pok. You can customise your order to suit your preferences, like no fish cake, or no meat ball, etc. I like it without ketchup or chilli, and a little bit of black vinegar. Brings out the original taste of the noodles and meat. Noodles are cooked well, springy and not too overdone, which is the way I like it. Highly recommended if you are looking for a place for breakfast along this road.
Very nice simple bowl of mee pok. No overpowering ingredients. Old school taste.
Old school simple but awesome Mee Pok. Balanced taste that needs slow savoring
Old school fish ball noodle. Taste is ok and typical
